<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 10:14AM AST  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms over the coastal waters of Saint Croix and
over Saint Croix...
At 1010 AM AST, Strong thunderstorms over Saint Croix are producing
frequent lightning and gusty winds. Small hail is possible as well.
These thunderstorms will continue to prevail across the local area
during the next hour or so.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
